<subSubSection id="B3E819AF0021D97AFCD7E800FABE0E59" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="7" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph id="FB4D4A240021D97AFCD7E800FB530C17" blockId="7.[810,1452,1839,2093]" lastBlockId="8.[810,1452,791,1846]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="7" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="C98696360021D975FCD7E800FC760069" bold="true" box="[863,1009,2066,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="127">Description.</emphasis>
(Based on 
<typeStatus id="2449F4860021D975FBF4E800FB590069" box="[1148,1246,2066,2092]" pageId="7" pageNumber="127">holotype</typeStatus>
otherwise stated) 
<materialsCitation id="4B9A4079002ED97AFF00E30BFB570C17" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3763881310" collectionCode="R, RS, T" county="Ovipositor straight" location="Legs" municipality="Metasoma" pageId="8" pageNumber="128" specimenCount="5" typeStatus="paratype">
Female. Color dark fuscous, legs paler. Body with no surface sculpture and prominent vestiture discernible. Head elongate as preserved (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFE7BE370FDDC0B39" box="[499,603,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[136,235,675,699]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,652]" captionTargetId="figure-600@8.[151,1436,181,652]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Paratype specimen no QBC-16C. A, Photograph of head, dorsal view. B, Photograph of metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530431/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Figs 7A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFDF8E370FD130B39" box="[624,660,866,892]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">8A</figureCitation>
, both on 
<typeStatus id="2449F486002ED97AFF00E395FF6F0BE4" box="[136,232,903,929]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">paratype</typeStatus>
QBC-16C) (possibly due to deformation), with eyes small, not much convex, placed before middle of head sides (more rostrally). Antenna 11-segmented [
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFF07E3E1FF740C4B" box="[143,243,1011,1038]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Figs 8A</figureCitation>
(
<typeStatus id="2449F486002ED97AFE83E3E6FEEA0C4B" box="[267,365,1012,1038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">paratype</typeStatus>
QBC-16C), 8D (
<typeStatus id="2449F486002ED97AFDC2E3E1FD330C4B" box="[586,692,1011,1038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
)], with scape long and wide, about as long as next three or four antennomeres combined, pedicel shorter than some apical segments, flagellum wide, somewhat flattened, slightly narrowing toward base, most segments longer than wide, basal flagellomere slightly longer than next one. Distinct subequal mandibles, right with three teeth and left with two ones. Of maxillary (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFE07E4E0FE640D49" box="[399,483,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
) and labial palps (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFD2FE4E0FD7C0D49" box="[679,763,1266,1292]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
), only their elongate apical segments visible. Mesosoma with dorsal pronotal part apparently short, mesoscutellum in side view with hind part somewhat elevated,metascutum forming high step above wide trough of metapostnotum, propodeum short, gently arching toward metasomal base in side view, transridged. Forewing (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFDA7E5DEFD010DA3" box="[559,646,1484,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
) with C, 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFD7FE5DFFC8D0DA2" box="[759,778,1485,1511]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">R</collectionCode>
behind pterostigma, 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFEFBE5E3FE120E4E" box="[371,405,1521,1547]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">RS</collectionCode>
before and behind 2r-rs (except for short section forming “ 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFE53E607FE680E6A" box="[475,495,1557,1583]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">T</collectionCode>
” pattern together with 2r-rs), M+Cu and M lost as pigmented veins or nearly so; 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFF3CE64CFF400E3D" box="[180,199,1630,1656]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">R</collectionCode>
and pterostigma tubular; 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFE72E64CFD9A0E3D" box="[506,541,1630,1656]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">RS</collectionCode>
&amp;M, 2r-rs and 1-Cu nebulous; pterostigma high (distinctly less than twice as long as wide), together with 2r-rs enclosed in lightly pigmented area; 2r-rs half as long as pterostigma wide; all membrane covered with short setae (margin included). Hind wing (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFE99E706FEE10F6B" box="[273,358,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8F</figureCitation>
) with only 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFE64E706FE780F6B" box="[492,511,1812,1838]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">R</collectionCode>
pigmented (tubular), 
<collectionCode id="9DE3D2E1002ED97AFD7FE706FC8D0F6B" box="[759,778,1812,1838]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">R</collectionCode>
apex with three hamuli, hind margin with fringe of long setae. 
<location id="FE2D1CFF002ED97AFF59E74FFE800F32" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:735BFB320020D97AFF00E726FB5F0F73:FE2D1CFF002ED97AFF59E74FFE800F32" box="[209,263,1885,1911]" county="Ovipositor straight" municipality="Metasoma" name="Legs" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Legs</location>
ordinary except that fore tibial spur (calcar) straight except bent subapical with bifid apex (
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFD29E793FD7B0FDE" box="[673,764,1921,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
), and fore basitarsus excised almost for all its length and with single row of setae along excision; tibial spurs 1: 1: 2; tibiae and tarsomeres 1–4 with stiff apical setae, mid and hind tibiae also with thick setae ventrally in distal half or so, basitarsi shorter than or (fore basitarsus) subequal to tarsomeres 2–4 combined, tarsomeres 3–4 almost equal in length, elongate, claw simple, arolium about as long as claw. 
<collectingMunicipality id="1B29D05E002ED97AFCE6E396FC640BDB" box="[878,995,900,926]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Metasoma</collectingMunicipality>
with petiolar segments very long, with no rough sculpture apparent, first segment slightly longer (in 
<typeStatus id="2449F486002ED97AFCD9E3D9FC320BA3" box="[849,949,971,998]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
) or shorter (in QBC-16C) than second [
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFAF0E3D9FCCA0C4F" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[136,235,675,699]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,652]" captionTargetId="figure-600@8.[151,1436,181,652]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Paratype specimen no QBC-16C. A, Photograph of head, dorsal view. B, Photograph of metasoma, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530431/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Figs 7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFCDFE3E2FCE80C4F" box="[855,879,1008,1034]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">8I</figureCitation>
(in QBC-16C), 8H (
<typeStatus id="2449F486002ED97AFBDAE3FDFB3B0C4F" box="[1106,1212,1007,1034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">holotype</typeStatus>
)], petiolar attachment to gaster frontal. 
<collectingCounty id="122C32A8002ED97AFC73E401FB510C68" box="[1019,1238,1043,1069]" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Ovipositor straight</collectingCounty>
, partially external (longest visible in QBC-16C, 
<figureCitation id="63C956A1002ED97AFBF1E425FB410C17" box="[1145,1222,1079,1106]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[136,235,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,202,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-145@9.[151,1436,189,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Leptoserphites iriae Rasnitsyn &amp; Azar, gen. et sp. nov. Drawings. A, Head, dorsal view, paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. B, Maxillary palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. C, Labial palp of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. D, Antenna of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. E, Forewing of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. F, Hind wing of paratype, specimen no QBC- 16C. G, Cleaning apparatus of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. H, Petiole of holotype, specimen no QBC-16A. I, Metasoma of paratype, specimen no QBC-16C. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6530433" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6530433/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8I</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
